The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 RIL fixes preferential price at Rs 1402

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, Feb. 26: Reliance Industries Ltd (RIL) today announced that its promoters would pick up shares in the company at Rs 1,402 a piece. RIL is issuing 12 crore warrants to its promoters in a preferential allotment that are convertible into equal number of shares. 

 On Saturday, RILs board had approved the preferential allotment. At the price of Rs 1402 per share, the value of these warrants work out to Rs 16,824 crore. 

 In a statement issued today, RIL said it would seek its shareholders consent through a postal ballot. The price of Rs 1,402 per share, it revealed, is the average of the weekly high and low of the closing prices of the RIL shares on the National Stock Exchange during the two weeks preceding the relevant date, February 27. 

 According to RIL, Rs 1,253 per share is the average of the weekly high and low of the closing prices of the companys shares quoted on the NSE in the six months preceding the relevant date. 

 RIL said an amount equivalent to 10 per cent of the price would be paid on allotment of warrants and the remaining 90 per cent would be paid at the time of subscription to shares on exercise of rights attached to the warrants within 18 months. 

 On exercise of such rights, the paid up capital of RIL will increase to Rs 1,513 crore from Rs 1,393 crore. 

 RIL is also coming out with an overseas issue. Both of the moves are primarily to fund its exploration and production activities. RIL is also building an integrated cracker and petrochemicals complex in the special economic zone (SEZ) at Jamnagar. This will be adjacent to the refinery that is being set up its subsidiary-Reliance Petroleum Ltd.




